---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE_URL } from '../../lib/seo/site';

const title = 'Terms of Use';
const description = 'Terms for using the Brand Semantics website.';
const lastUpdated = 'February 8, 2026';

const page = {
  title,
  description,
  url: `${SITE_URL}/legal/terms`,
  breadcrumbs: [
    { name: 'Home', url: `${SITE_URL}/` },
    { name: 'Terms', url: `${SITE_URL}/legal/terms` }
  ]
};
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} page={page}>
  <section class="container-narrow py-16">
    <div class="eyebrow">Legal</div>
    <h1 class="mt-4 text-4xl font-semibold text-ink">Terms of Use</h1>
    <div class="prose mt-6">
      <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> {lastUpdated}</p>
      <p>
        These Terms of Use (the “Terms”) apply to your access to and use of the Brand Semantics website (the “Site”),
        including pages under Services, Use Cases, Opinions, Resources, and Company (together, the “Content”).
        By accessing or using the Site, you agree to these Terms.
      </p>

      <h2>Who We Are</h2>
      <p>
        “Brand Semantics”, “we”, “us”, and “our” refer to the operator of this Site. If you need our legal entity name,
        registered address, or company number for contracting purposes, please contact us via the
        <a href="/company/contact">Contact</a> page.
      </p>

      <h2>Scope and Intended Audience</h2>
      <p>
        The Site is provided for informational purposes and is intended primarily for business and professional users.
        The Content does not constitute legal, financial, or professional advice. You are responsible for how you use it.
      </p>

      <h2>Permitted Use</h2>
      <p>
        We grant you a limited, non-exclusive, non-transferable, revocable licence to access and use the Site for your
        internal evaluation and business purposes, in accordance with these Terms.
      </p>
      <p>You may:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Browse and share links to pages on the Site.</li>
        <li>Quote short excerpts for commentary or internal review, with attribution to Brand Semantics.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>You may not:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Copy, reproduce, republish, sell, license, or commercially exploit the Content without written permission.</li>
        <li>Scrape, crawl, or harvest the Site at scale (including by automated means) except where permitted by law.</li>
        <li>Reverse engineer or attempt to bypass any access controls, rate limits, or security measures.</li>
        <li>Use the Site in a way that interferes with its availability, integrity, or performance.</li>
        <li>Misrepresent your affiliation with Brand Semantics or use the Site to transmit unlawful, harmful, or deceptive content.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Intellectual Property</h2>
      <p>
        The Site and Content are protected by intellectual property laws. Brand Semantics, IBOM™, and any associated logos
        are trademarks or trade names of Brand Semantics and/or its licensors. All rights not expressly granted are reserved.
      </p>

      <h2>User Submissions</h2>
      <p>
        If you submit information through a form or otherwise provide feedback (a “Submission”), you confirm that:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>You have the rights needed to provide the Submission.</li>
        <li>Your Submission does not infringe third-party rights or contain unlawful material.</li>
        <li>You do not include sensitive personal data unless we expressly request it.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        You grant us a non-exclusive, worldwide, royalty-free licence to use your Submission for the purpose of responding,
        improving the Site, and operating our services. We will handle personal data in accordance with our
        <a href="/legal/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Third-Party Links and Services</h2>
      <p>
        The Site may reference third-party websites, tools, or services. We do not control and are not responsible for them.
        Your use of third-party services is governed by their terms and policies.
      </p>

      <h2>Availability, Changes, and Termination</h2>
      <p>
        We may modify, suspend, or discontinue any part of the Site at any time. We may also update these Terms by posting a
        revised version on this page. Continued use of the Site after an update means you accept the updated Terms.
      </p>

      <h2>Disclaimers</h2>
      <p>
        The Site and Content are provided “as is” and “as available”. To the maximum extent permitted by law, we disclaim all
        warranties, express or implied, including implied warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and
        non-infringement. We do not warrant that the Site will be uninterrupted, secure, or error-free.
      </p>

      <h2>Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the maximum extent permitted by law, Brand Semantics will not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special,
        consequential, or punitive damages, or for any loss of profits, revenue, data, goodwill, or business opportunity,
        arising out of or related to your use of (or inability to use) the Site.
      </p>
      <p>
        Where liability cannot be excluded, our total liability for all claims relating to the Site will be limited to the
        amount you paid to access the Site in the 12 months before the event giving rise to the claim (if any).
      </p>

      <h2>Indemnity</h2>
      <p>
        You agree to indemnify and hold harmless Brand Semantics from any claims, damages, liabilities, and expenses arising
        from your misuse of the Site, your Submissions, or your breach of these Terms.
      </p>

      <h2>Governing Law</h2>
      <p>
        These Terms are governed by the laws of England and Wales, and the courts of England and Wales will have exclusive
        jurisdiction, except where applicable law provides otherwise.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about these Terms? Contact us via <a href="/company/contact">Get in touch</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
